Package com.intellij.util.xml

Class Converter<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.intellij.util.xml.Converter<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - Type to convert from/to.
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AntBooleanConverter, AntDomDefaultTargetConverter, AntDomRefIdConverter, AntDomTargetDependsListConverter, AntMultiPathStringConverter, AntPathConverter, CanonicalPsiTypeConverter, CharacterValueConverter, ClassValueConverter, JvmPsiTypeConverter, PathReferenceConverter, PsiClassConverter, PsiPackageConverter, ResolvingConverter, RngHrefConverter, WrappingConverter

    public abstract class Converter<T>
extends java.lang.Object
    Base DOM class to convert objects of a definite type into String and back. Most often used with Convert annotation with methods returning GenericDomValue<T>.
    See Also:
    ResolvingConverter, CustomReferenceConverter
